	dprr:hasNoteText "Became a byword for accepting bribes while presiding over the quaestio de sicariis. Went into exile when prosecuted by Scaevola (see 141) and took poison when recalled (Cic. Att. 12.5b; ND 1.63- Lucil. 1312 M; 3.74; Fin. 2.54; 4.77; 5.62; Ascon. 23 C; Gell. 2.7.20)." .
